From: Christopher L. Crutchfield <ccrutchf@ucsd.edu>
Date: Sat, 02 May 2026 12:50:00 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] ufs: exynos: gs201: enable PRDT prefetch on TX without
 requiring crypto

`exynos_ufs_post_link` only ORs `PRDT_PREFETCH_EN` (BIT(31)) into
`HCI_TXPRDT_ENTRY_SIZE` when `hba->caps & UFSHCD_CAP_CRYPTO` is set.
On gs201 we don't currently get `UFSHCD_CAP_CRYPTO` because the
gs201 path can't go through `EXYNOS_UFS_OPT_UFSPR_SECURE` (BL31's
`SMC_CMD_FMP_SECURITY` / `SMC_CMD_SMU(SMU_INIT)` don't actually
program the FMP security registers, so fmp_init early-returns and
crypto registration never happens). The result is that mainline gs201
runs with TX-PRDT prefetch DISABLED — the controller fetches PRDT
entries on demand, one at a time, instead of batch-prefetching them
into its internal cache.

AOSP's downstream driver (`google-modules/soc/gs/drivers/ufs/ufs-exynos.c`,
`exynos_ufs_config_host`) writes
`PRDT_PREFECT_EN | PRDT_SET_SIZE(12)` to `HCI_TXPRDT_ENTRY_SIZE`
unconditionally for every Tensor SoC, with no dependency on
crypto/inline-encryption being available. The bit gates an AXI master
optimisation that's orthogonal to crypto.

Add an explicit write in `gs201_ufs_post_link` that overwrites the
generic exynos_ufs_post_link value with the AOSP-equivalent
`PRDT_PREFETCH_EN | size = 12`. gs201 only — gs101 uses the existing
`gs101_ufs_post_link` which doesn't apply this fix because gs101
mainline gets `UFSHCD_CAP_CRYPTO` through the working
`EXYNOS_UFS_OPT_UFSPR_SECURE` path. (Verifying gs101 separately would
be a good cleanup — AOSP shares the config_host code across
gs101/gs201/zuma.)

**Important caveat:** this matches AOSP byte-for-byte but does NOT
on its own resolve the gs201 SCSI hang at ~38 s into boot at PWM gear
that we're still seeing on a forked (HS-Rate-B-disabled) tree.
PRDT prefetch is an AXI-master efficiency feature; the wedge has the
shape of a controller-level race in PWM gear that survives every
SCSI-side and HCI-side workaround we've tried, including this one.
The patch stands on its own as "match AOSP behaviour"; PWM survival
is a separate problem.

Signed-off-by: Christopher L. Crutchfield <ccrutchf@ucsd.edu>
Cc: Peter Griffin <peter.griffin@linaro.org>
Cc: Alim Akhtar <alim.akhtar@samsung.com>
Cc: linux-samsung-soc@vger.kernel.org
Cc: linux-scsi@vger.kernel.org
Cc: linux-arm-kernel@lists.infradead.org
---
 drivers/ufs/host/ufs-exynos.c | 14 ++++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 14 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/ufs/host/ufs-exynos.c b/drivers/ufs/host/ufs-exynos.c
--- a/drivers/ufs/host/ufs-exynos.c
+++ b/drivers/ufs/host/ufs-exynos.c
@@ -2400,6 +2400,20 @@ static int gs201_ufs_post_link(struct exynos_ufs *ufs)
 	unipro_writel(ufs, 0x0, 0x3348);
 	unipro_writel(ufs, 0x0, 0x334C);

+	/*
+	 * Enable TX PRDT prefetch (BIT(31) of HCI_TXPRDT_ENTRY_SIZE).
+	 * exynos_ufs_post_link only ORs this bit in when CRYPTO is enabled
+	 * (val |= PRDT_PREFETCH_EN under hba->caps & UFSHCD_CAP_CRYPTO),
+	 * but on gs201 we cannot enable EXYNOS_UFS_OPT_UFSPR_SECURE (BL31
+	 * doesn't honour the FMP SMC pair) so CRYPTO is never set and TX
+	 * PRDT prefetch ships disabled. AOSP's exynos_ufs_config_host
+	 * writes PRDT_PREFECT_EN unconditionally for every Tensor SoC;
+	 * match that behaviour explicitly.
+	 */
+	hci_writel(ufs,
+		   PRDT_PREFETCH_EN | (ilog2(DATA_UNIT_SIZE) & 0x1F),
+		   HCI_TXPRDT_ENTRY_SIZE);
+
 	return 0;
 }

--
